This paper is primarily focused on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their ability to handle deformations in images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the adjustments made to the network during training, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the assumptions made about neural networks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the role of pooling layers in CNNs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of rigorous empirical testing, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
